HEADWORD: Cutlery
<hw>Cut"ler*y</hw> <pr>(k⟦ucr⟧t"l⟦etil⟧r*⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The business of a cutler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Edged or cutting instruments, collectively,
especially knives for cutting food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>eating utensils such as knives, forks, and
spoons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cutlet</ent>⟦br⟧
